<i>Posted by Seprentor Nevermore on 02-01-2002 09:31 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>As soon as you zone into Neriak from Nektulos, enter zone a little and go to the right. From there, you shimmy up the wall (there is plenty of room to do this), and from there you have a good view of 3 light blue guards, and 3 casters. You can single pull them with a bow and arrow from there. All have an extremley high MR, but aren't too tough. I wouldnt suggest this solo, either. Its a good camp for a war/cler/ranger. After those 6 mobs are killed, you can pull the two front guards. You'll probably have respawns by this point, but if you're fast enough, you can pull the dark blue dark elf just inside the gates. He's a SK that's quite a bit tougher than the others, but nothing you shouldnt be able to handle at 51 or so. Loot is ok, plenty of fine steel, couple pp each kill, and all three casters drop Robes of Enshroudment (necro robe). Robe is lore, so no farming )  Anyway, it is easy, and yes, exp here is pretty nice, although it can get a little boring....<p><FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2">__________________<br>
Seprentor Nevermore<br />
1st season Outrider<br />
Coven of Lore<br />
A Brell Serilis Guild</font></p></p>
