<i>Posted by Tillamook Spiritwind on 02-04-2002 04:24 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Okay, so here is a lil spoiler info on Neriak.  If your hearing about xping in 3rd gate to lvl 55 its gonna be on the DE mages at the area across the water that is kinda near the necro/sk guild more then likely.  This is kinda slow xp but not bad if your just topping off to ding 55.  The reason you hear about that spot being good to lvl 55 is because its got 3 mages that give xp until you ding 55.  You do NOT need to be non-kos to fight there and cr is easy with invis.  I never heard of a ranger soloing there but I have heard of necros/mages/druids soloing there.  Prolly a good spot for a beastlord as well.<br />
If you want xp in Neriak to say lvl 58, although the mobs I am about to talk about are still blue to me at 60, try the SK/Necro faction ogres and trolls in Neriak A in the building over near the arena.  These can easily be fear kited if you fix your faction with the Neriak guards by doing the wine quest in NeriakC.  With a high enough cleric you can get decent xp on these because you can easily split them and they respawn quickly enough to make for constant killing.  If your faction is fixed the Neriak guards will ignore the fighting and leave you to your bidness.  BTW, fixing your faction will not fix your necro/sk, mage, cleric, rogue, etc faction.  So watch your step even though you can now bank and buy/sell from most vendors.<p><FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2">__________________<br>
<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net/"><img align="left" src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/logo.gif" border="0"></a><font color="#000080" size="2" face="Georgia">Tillamook Spiritwind</font><br />
<font color="#000080" size="2" face="Georgia"><i>Tunare's Enlightened One...</i><br />
