<hr>
<i>Posted by Norwolf on 03-07-2002 05:55 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I have started to hunt here at level 51 for fun when passing the time, and I always thought it would be great in infiltrate the DE city and hunt them.<br />
<br />
I have not gone to far in with my Ranger, but I have found a great spot to hunt near the main wall.<br />
<br />
Zone in and Inv up.<br />
<br />
Run through the main gate and go left toward the Oger / troll side, up the path but do not go into the tunnel to there instead hop on top of the rocks along the side wall.<br />
<br />
From here I have pulled guards from off the top wall where they will run down [thankfully not agroing anything along the way it seems] and up to the rock where I am, work them over and have a good snare on them and root ready when they walk away.<br />
<br />
easy kills so far but I have not taken on the casters on top of the wall .... yet...<br />
<br />
If things go bad while you are up on the rocks you can run to the wall where you are near level to it and jump over to the far side giving you time to zone before they DE's come around the wall to try and get you.<br />
<br />
Side notes:<br />
Its a good idea I think to get a DE character and take a look around to get comfortable with the area... in teh heat of it you want to be comfortable running around.<br />
<br />
What’s up with the Halfling dude in the water in the middle city zone??? first time I had seen him was the other day.<p><FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2">__________________<br>
